              "name": "What is Xero and why should Indian businesses consider it?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Xero is a New Zealand-based cloud accounting platform with 4.59 million global subscribers. Key advantages for India: fully cloud-based architecture (no desktop), excellent multi-currency on Premium plan for USD/EUR/GBP billing, 1,000+ app integrations (Stripe, Razorpay, Shopify), and a clean modern interface. Best suited for IT exporters, SaaS companies, startups, and foreign subsidiaries. Main limitation: no native Indian GST localisation."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Does Xero support Indian GST?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Xero supports GST tax rates and GST-compliant invoicing, but does not have native Indian GST features like direct GSTR-1 portal filing, GSTR-2B auto-reconciliation, IMS, or IRN e-invoicing. These are available in TallyPrime and Zoho Books natively. Indian businesses using Xero need a CA firm like Patron Accounting to manage compliance through a manual workflow or third-party add-ons."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "What is the price of Xero in India?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Xero does not have INR pricing. Indian businesses pay in USD: Starter $29/month (20 invoices, 5 bills), Standard $46/month (unlimited), Premium $69/month (adds multi-currency). All plans include unlimited users. 30-day free trial available. Patron Accounting CA service starts from INR 4,999/month separately. Premium recommended for most Indian use cases."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Is Xero better than TallyPrime for Indian businesses?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Depends on your business model. Xero is better for: foreign currency billing, cloud access from any device, Stripe/Shopify integrations, startups needing investor-grade accounting. TallyPrime is better for: domestic-only transactions, deep inventory management, native GSTR-1 filing and GSTR-2B reconciliation, one-time license cost. Patron Accounting helps evaluate which platform fits your situation."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Can Xero handle e-invoicing for India?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Xero does not have built-in IRP integration for India e-invoicing (mandatory above Rs 5 crore AATO). Patron Accounting handles this through third-party GST e-invoicing add-ons connecting Xero to IRP, or a CA-managed process exporting invoice data and generating IRNs on the portal. TallyPrime has a native advantage here for high-volume businesses."
              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "Is Xero suitable for Indian startups?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes. Xero is internationally recognised by investors in US, UK, and Singapore. Clean cloud interface for founders, app integrations with Stripe and Razorpay, multi-currency for foreign funding rounds, and investor-ready reporting. Patron Accounting sets up Xero correctly from day one, manages GST/TDS compliance, and prepares investor-ready MIS from Xero data. Quick Answers Q: Xero accounting kya hai India mein? Xero ek cloud-based accounting software hai jo 4.59 million businesses use karti hain globally. Indian businesses ke liye multi-currency billing aur app integrations best hain, lekin GST filing ke liye CA ki zaroorat hai. Q: Does Xero file GSTR-1 directly? No. Xero does not have native GSTR-1 portal filing. CA team exports sales data from Xero, classifies by section, and files on the GST portal manually. Q: Xero aur Tally mein kya antar hai? Xero cloud-based hai, multi-currency best hai, 1,000+ apps hain. Tally desktop-based hai, GST compliance native hai, inventory better hai. Export business ke liye Xero, domestic ke liye Tally recommend hai. Q: Xero se ITR kaise file kare? Xero se P&L aur Balance Sheet export karo, CA team ITR-3/5/6 prepare karke file karti hai. Tax audit Form 3CD ke liye Xero general ledger as audit trail use hota hai."
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
