<!-- SECTION 2: OVERVIEW / INTRO + TL;DR -->
<section class="content-section" id="overview-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Xero Accounting - CA-Managed Cloud Accounting for Indian Businesses</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
                    <p><strong>&#128204; TL;DR - Xero Accounting Services at a Glance</strong></p>
                    <p>Xero is a leading global cloud accounting platform with 4.59 million subscribers, offering excellent multi-currency support, 1,000+ app integrations, and a modern interface. But Xero does not have native Indian GST localisation - no GSTR-1 portal filing, no GSTR-2B auto-reconciliation, no IRN e-invoicing, and no TDS management. Patron Accounting bridges this compliance gap with CA-managed GST, TDS, and ITR services starting from INR 4,999 per month - giving you the best of Xero's global capabilities combined with complete Indian statutory compliance.</p>
                </div>
                <p>For Indian businesses, particularly IT companies, software exporters, SaaS platforms, and startups billing in USD, EUR, or AED, Xero offers a clean interface, real-time financial visibility, multi-currency support on the Premium plan ($69/month), and 1,000+ app integrations that TallyPrime cannot match. The Xero App Store connects with Stripe, Razorpay, Shopify, HubSpot, and hundreds of other platforms.</p>
                <p>However, the critical limitation for Indian businesses is that Xero has no built-in Indian GST localisation. There is no direct GSTR-1 upload, no automatic GSTR-2B ITC reconciliation, no IRN e-invoicing for the IRP, and no TDS management. Patron Accounting's CA team bridges every one of these gaps through a structured compliance process - configuring Xero correctly for Indian tax requirements and managing all returns and filings monthly.</p>
                <p>Content is reviewed quarterly for accuracy.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- SECTION 3: WHAT IS GSTAT APPEAL FILING -->
<section class="content-section" id="what-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="column-content">
                <h2 class="section-title">What is Xero Accounting?</h2>
                <div class="content-text what-is-definition">
                    
                    <p>Xero is a New Zealand-based cloud accounting software company founded in 2006, listed on the ASX (ASX: XRO), with 4.59 million subscribers globally across 180+ countries as of September 2025. In October 2025, Xero completed its acquisition of Melio Payments for USD 2.5 billion, expanding its accounts payable capabilities.</p><p>Xero is cloud-native and subscription-based - no desktop installation or server required. Key capabilities for Indian businesses include: <strong>single unified real-time ledger</strong> accessible from any device, <strong>automatic bank feeds</strong> from Indian banks, <strong>multi-currency invoicing</strong> in 160+ currencies on the Premium plan with automatic exchange gain/loss calculation, <strong>1,000+ app integrations</strong> (Stripe, Razorpay, Shopify, HubSpot), and <strong>real-time financial reports</strong> without waiting for month-end.</p><p>Xero established a technology centre in India in November 2022 in partnership with Infosys, reflecting India's growing importance to Xero's global operations. Syft Analytics (acquired by Xero in September 2024) provides advanced cloud-based reporting and dashboards built specifically for Xero data.</p>

                </div>
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <p><strong>Key Terms for Xero Accounting:</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Xero Premium Plan ($69/month):</strong> Essential tier for Indian businesses - adds multi-currency invoicing in 160+ currencies with live exchange rates and automatic gain/loss calculation</p><p><strong>India GST Compliance Layer:</strong> CA-managed process bridging Xero's lack of native GSTR-1 filing, GSTR-2B reconciliation, e-invoicing, and TDS - provided entirely by Patron Accounting</p><p><strong>Xero Bank Feeds:</strong> Automatic daily import of transactions from connected Indian bank accounts for real-time reconciliation with single-click matching</p><p><strong>FIRC/BRC Reconciliation:</strong> Matching Foreign Inward Remittance Certificates against Xero export invoices for LUT compliance and zero-rated GST claims</p><p><strong>Xero App Store (1,000+ integrations):</strong> Connects Stripe, Razorpay, Shopify, HubSpot, Hubdoc, Gusto, and more - far more options than TallyPrime</p>

